  "title": "Customer Relations Officer / Assistant Customer Relations Officer",
  "description": "<ul><li>Minimum GCE “A” Level with 2-3 years of public relations experiences preferably in Home Improvement Program (HIP) projects.</li><li>He/ She shall be capable of communicating effectively in English and one other official language.</li><li>Possesses computer skills in Microsoft Office, Word, Excel and PPT.</li><li>B. Responsibilities and Duties:</li><li>Capable of taking instruction from Client’s Rep, consultants and contractor’s project manager as and when required or directed.</li><li>CRO shall be competent and possesses the skill, knowledge and ability to manage the public relations issues and general project queries with residents effectively.</li><li>He/ She shall possess good communication and interpersonal skills in liaising with subcontractors in day-to-day’s work activities and project stakeholders (HDB, Town Council and Consultants) pertaining to the project/ resident’s matters.</li><li> CRO shall generate the HIP block schedule and units work schedules in good times to aid the materials & manpower resources planning.</li><li>Manning the Information Centre Counter operations and Information Hotline.</li><li>Attend to residents’ defect feedback or query and making appointment with owner for a visit or joint inspection by RTO and Supervisor. Making appointment for Supervisor to attend the defect rectification and monitoring of work done for defect closure.</li><li>Draft and reply to feedback/ queries and message from residents within stipulated timeframes.</li></ul><p>C. Administrative, Recording & Documentations</p><ul><li>CRO shall be in-charge of proper recording and filing of vital documents required by HDB, forms and records, and photos into HICS.</li><li>He/ she shall attend and provide administrative assistance and logistic supports in the Working Committee Meeting (Construction Phase) as and when directed by Client’s Rep or Consultants.</li></ul>",
